      • addMapViewAndAttachToWindow

        public static com.locuslabs.sdk.internal.maps.controller.MapViewController.Builder addMapViewAndAttachToWindow(com.locuslabs.sdk.javascriptintegration.JavaScriptEnvironment javaScriptEnvironment)
        This static method is intended to mirror the instance method Map.addMapView(OnMapViewReadyListener). Whereas Map.addMapView(OnMapViewReadyListener) gets called when customers employ the Classic Load protocol, addMapViewAndAttachToWindow(com.locuslabs.sdk.javascriptintegration.JavaScriptEnvironment) gets called when customers employ the Fast Load protocol. With Classic Load, the customer's code has access to an instance of DefaultMap but not so with Fast Load because the DefaultMap doesn't get instantiated until after the customer's code attaches the view hierarchy.

        Instantiates a MapViewController.Builder which holds a WebView and passes the Builder back to the customers' code so the customer can attach the WebView to the view hierarchy. This is necessary for the WebView to access WebGL because WebGL is a hardware acceleration graphics feature and as such it requires the view actuall to be on-screen.

        The Builder's work of constructing a MapViewController is finished by DefaultMap(MapViewController.Builder, DefaultVenue, JavaScriptMap, JavaScriptMapView)

        Parameters:
        javaScriptEnvironment -
        Returns:
